Problem 1: Age Eligibility and Type Conversion
Ask the user to enter their birth year. Calculate their age assuming current year is 2026.
Check if the person is:
• 18 years or older
• Age less than or equal to 60
Print:
• Age
• Whether the person belongs to the “working age group”.


#!/bin/bash
currentyear=2026
read -p " Enter your birth year:  " birthyear
age=$(("$currentyear"-"$birthyear"))
echo "age of user is $age. "
if [ $age -le 18 ]; then
        echo "User is underage"
elif [ $age -le 60 ]; then
        echo "User belongs to working age group"
else
        echo "User older then 60 years"
fi